FBIS3-25604 "drafr036_a_94006" FBIS-AFR-94-036 Document Type:Daily Report 23 February 1994 CENTRAL AFRICA Gabon PDG Member Killed AB2302100094 Libreville RTG Chaine Nationale Radio Network in French 0800 GMT 23 Feb 94 AB2302100094 Libreville RTG Chaine Nationale Radio Network in French 0800 GMT 23 Feb 94 Language: French Article Type:BFN [Text] Political violence broke out in Libreville yesterday. Radio-Tele Liberte was destroyed early yesterday morning by the Armed Forces, which stormed the radio station located at Terre-Nouvelle. After Radio-Tele Liberte was destroyed, opposition supporters retaliated by killing (Jean Kamougue-Komo), a member of the Gabonese Democratic Party [PDG]. The government daily L'UNION has reported the death of an unidentified person at Yayi crossroads, who was killed as the security forces were destroying a barricade. Tension has been high in Libreville since 21 February when the Federation of Free Trade Unions called for an indefinite general strike.
